import glob

path = 'amazon-products-dataset'
all_files = glob.glob(path + "/*.csv")
In [5]:
dfs = []
In [6]:
for file in all_files:
    df = pd.read_csv(file, index_col=None, header=0)
    dfs.append(df)
In [7]:
amazon_df = pd.concat(dfs, axis=0, ignore_index=True)

The Home & kitchen category have 1 unsual product which discount percented is 99.99%. So I gonna exclude that main category to make the data more reliable.

In [61]:
ax= amazon_df.query('main_category != "home & kitchen"') \
    .groupby('main_category')['actual_price'] \
    .agg(['mean','count']) \
    .query('count > 5000') \
    .sort_values('mean', ascending=False)['mean'] \
    .plot(kind='barh', title='Ranking main category by average price')
ax.set_xlabel('Average price (USD)')
ax.set_ylabel('Main Category')
plt.show()

6. Sumarize and Conclusion¶

This dataset contain total 142 difference categories. After investigate into this dataset, we can learn many things.

  1. Accessories is the main category which has most products in Amazon, most ratings is at 4.0, and average price is approximate 37 USD.
  2. Home & kitchen has the highest average price at 9500 USD, which has 1 unsual product have 99.99% discount.
